/wiki/Naga,_Camarines_Sur: Naga, officially the City of Naga (Central Bikol: Ciudad nin Naga; Rinconada Bikol: Syudad ka Naga; Tagalog: Lungsod ng Naga; Spanish: Ciudad de Naga), or simply referred to as  Naga City, is a 2nd class independent component city in the Bicol Region, Philippines. According to the 2015 census, it has a population of 196,003 people.
/wiki/Camarines_Sur: Camarines Sur (Central Bicolano: Habagatan na Camarines; Tagalog: Timog Camarines) is a province located in the Bicol Region in Luzon of the Philippines. Its capital is Pili and the province borders Camarines Norte and Quezon to the northwest, and Albay to the south. To the east lies the island province of Catanduanes across the Maqueda Channel.
/wiki/Legazpi,_Albay: Legazpi, officially the City of Legazpi, (Central Bicolano: Ciudad nin Legazpi; Tagalog: Lungsod ng Legazpi; Spanish: Ciudad de Legazpi) and often referred to as Legazpi City, is a 1st Class component city and the capital of the province of Albay in the Philippines. According to the 2015 census, it has a population of 196,639. Legazpi is the regional center and largest city of the Bicol Region, in terms of population. It is the region's center of tourism, education, health services, commerce and transportation in the Bicol Region.
/wiki/Albay: Albay  (Central Bicolano: Probinsya kan Albay; Tagalog: Lalawigan ng Albay; Spanish: Provincia de Albay) is a province located in the Bicol Region in southeastern Luzon of the Philippines.
/wiki/Ayala_Malls_Legazpi: Ayala Malls Legazpi is a shopping mall developed and managed by Ayala Malls in partnership with Bicol-based retail group LCC Group of Companies. It is located along Quezon Avenue in Barangay Capantawan, Legazpi City, Albay. It is the first Ayala Mall in the Bicol Region. Ayala Malls Legazpi opened on April 19, 2016 and has a gross leasable area of 32,000 m2 (340,000 sq ft)
/wiki/Daet,_Camarines_Norte: Daet (IPA: [daʔet]), officially the Municipality of Daet,  is a 1st class municipality and capital of the province of Camarines Norte, Philippines. According to the 2015 census, it has a population of 104,799 people.
/wiki/Camarines_Norte: Camarines Norte (Central Bicolano: Amihanan na Camarines; Tagalog: Hilagang Camarines) is a province located in the Bicol region in Luzon of the Philippines. Its capital is Daet. The province borders Quezon to the west, Camarines Sur to the south, and the Philippine Sea to the north.
/wiki/Sorsogon_City: Sorsogon City, officially the City of Sorsogon, (Central Bicolano: Ciudad nin Sorsogon; Tagalog: Lungsod ng Sorsogon), is a 3rd class city and capital of the province of Sorsogon, Philippines. According to the 2015 census, it has a population of 168,110 people.
/wiki/Masbate_City: Masbate City, officially the City of Masbate, (Masbateño: Syudad san Masbate; Hiligaynon: Dakbanwa sang Masbate; Cebuano: Dakbayan sa Masbate/Syudad sa Masbate; Central Bicolano: Ciudad nin Masbate; Tagalog: Lungsod ng Masbate) is a 4th class city and capital of the province of Masbate, Philippines. According to the 2015 census, it has a population of 95,389 people.
/wiki/Iriga: Iriga, officially the City of Iriga, (Rinconada Bikol: Syudad ka Iriga; Central Bicolano: Syudad nin Iriga; Tagalog: Lungsod ng Iriga), or simply referred to as Iriga City, is a 4th class city in the province of Camarines Sur, Philippines. According to the 2015 census, it has a population of 111,757 people.
/wiki/Libmanan,_Camarines_Sur: Libmanan, officially the Municipality of Libmanan,  is a 1st class municipality in the province of Camarines Sur, Philippines. According to the 2015 census, it has a population of 108,716 people. The town is home to the Morales Ruins, a 1937 architectural Art Deco masterpiece in the heart of the historic town. The Art Deco building is reportedly designed by a Filipino national artist.
/wiki/Goa,_Camarines_Sur: Goa, officially the Municipality of Goa,  is a 2nd class municipality in the province of Camarines Sur, Philippines. According to the 2015 census, it has a population of 63,308 people.
/wiki/Pili,_Camarines_Sur: Pili, officially the Municipality of Pili, (Central Bicolano: Banwaan kan Ocampo), Rinconada Bikol: Banwāan ka Ocampo, Tagalog: Bayan ng Ocampo) is a 1st class municipality and capital of the province of Camarines Sur, Philippines.
/wiki/Calabanga,_Camarines_Sur: Calabanga, officially the Municipality of Calabanga,  is a 1st class municipality in the province of Camarines Sur, Philippines. According to the 2015 census, it has a population of 83,033 people.
